:: M-B-0 {"position":"700,400","size":"100,100"}
(set: $viewed to it + (a: "MB"))
(set: $heard_sam_sentence to true)

Samael was still standing where you first saw him, next to the car, like he hadn't moved since you pulled in. His hands were shaking and he kept wiping them on his pants like they were wet. When he saw you coming he straightened up a little, tried to pull himself together, but his face was grey and his eyes kept drifting back toward the open bay.

(live: 3s)[(stop:)"I came in early," he said, before you even asked. "I just— I had some stuff to take care of. I came in and the garage was closed, and I opened it and he was just— he was in the car, and I tried to wake him up but he wasn't..." He trailed off and pressed the heel of his hand against his forehead. His voice sounded like he'd been rehearsing it in his head for the last twenty minutes and still couldn't get it to come out right.

[[Push him->M-B-1]]
[[Let it go->M-B-2]]
]


:: M-B-1 {"position":"800,300","size":"100,100"}
(set: $clues_found to it + 1)

You asked him why he really came in early. His face changed, just for a second, something between fear and anger flashing across it before he got it under control.

"I told you, I had stuff to take care of."

You didn't say anything. You just waited. The silence did more than another question would have.

"I don't know what you want me to say," he said, quieter now. He wouldn't look at you. His hands were still shaking and he shoved them in his pockets like that would make it stop.

[[He said it almost to himself->M-B-3]]


:: M-B-2 {"position":"800,500","size":"100,100"}
You nodded and didn't press it.

He looked relieved in a way that felt too big for the moment, like you'd just let him off a hook he thought he'd never get free of.

He took a breath and steadied himself. When he spoke again, his voice was flatter, more controlled.

[[He said it almost to himself->M-B-3]]


:: M-B-3 {"position":"900,400","size":"100,100"}
"David was oddly tired and could fall asleep anywhere like that. I'm not surprised he, you know." He gestured vaguely at the car. "He was probably exhausted. Fell asleep with the engine on, and that was it."

(if: $saw_pre_coaching is true)[Something cold moved through you.

You had heard those words before. Almost exactly.

The same phrasing. "Oddly tired." "Like that."

(set: $saw_A_influence_B to true)]

He stared at the ground and didn't say anything else.

[[You left him there by the car->Morning-Bottleneck]]


:: M-C-0 {"position":"700,600","size":"100,100"}
(set: $viewed to it + (a: "MC"))

Cassandra was already outside when you got there, sitting on the curb by the front entrance with her knees pulled up and her phone in her hand, not looking at it, just holding it like she needed something solid. She looked up when she saw you and started talking before you could say anything.

(live: 3s)[(stop:)"I don't understand how this happened, he was fine last night, he was laughing, you saw him, everyone saw him, he was fine." She kept repeating it like if she said it enough times it would undo something. Her eyes were red and her voice had that flat, shaky quality of someone who had already cried and come out the other side into something worse.

How do you respond?

(link: "Just listen")[You stood there and let her talk. She wasn't really asking you to do anything else.

[[She kept going->M-C-1]]]
]


:: M-C-1 {"position":"900,600","size":"100,100"}
"I keep going over last night trying to figure out what I missed, you know? Like was there a sign and I just didn't see it." She wiped her face with the back of her hand and stared at the parking lot. "He was in a good mood when the ticket hit, everyone was, and then I guess toward the end of the night he started getting kind of quiet, kind of sluggish, and I remember thinking he just looked exhausted, like he'd been running on nothing all week and it finally caught up."

She pulled at a thread on her sleeve. "And then I was leaving and I walked past the break room and Abby and Sam were in there talking, and I heard Abby say something like 'David was oddly tired and could fall asleep anywhere like that,' and I remember thinking yeah, exactly, that's what I was noticing too."

(set: $saw_pre_coaching to true)

(if: $heard_sam_sentence is true)[Something about hearing those words made your stomach drop.

You had heard them already. Almost exactly.

The same phrasing. The same shape.

(set: $saw_A_influence_B to true)]

(live: 5s)[(stop:)She was quiet for a second. "I should have checked on him. I don't know what I would have done, but I should have checked."

She looked down at her phone again, turning it over in her hands.

[[You stayed with her until you couldn't anymore->Morning-Bottleneck]]]


:: M-D-0 {"position":"700,800","size":"100,100"}
{
(set: $clues_found to it + 2)
(set: $saw_pills to true)
(set: $viewed to it + (a: "MD"))
}
Everyone was outside, gathered around the garage or standing in the parking lot in small clusters trying to figure out what to do with themselves. Nobody was watching the building. You weren't sure what you were looking for when you went inside, maybe just somewhere to stand that didn't have a dead man in it, but your feet took you down the hall toward David's office like they knew something you didn't.

(live: 3s)[(stop:)The door was open. It was always open, David never closed it, he said it made him feel like a real boss and he didn't like that. Everything looked the same as it always did, the messy desk, the coffee mug with the chip in the rim, the jacket hanging off the back of his chair like he'd be back in five minutes to put it on. You stood in the doorway for a second and felt something tighten in your chest that you didn't want to name.]

(live: 7s)[(stop:)You stepped inside. You weren't sure why. There was a crumpled napkin in your hand from the coffee you'd grabbed on the way in and you tossed it toward the trash can by the desk, missed, bent down to pick it up, and that's when you saw it.

An unlabeled pill bottle sitting right on top of the garbage, not buried, not hidden, just tossed in like someone had done it recently. You picked it up before you thought about it. It was empty. Next to where it had been, crumpled but readable, was a receipt from a gas station about ten minutes from the office, timestamped from last night. The items listed were a bag of chips and a box of over-the-counter sleep aid.]

(live: 11s)[(stop:)You stood there with the bottle in your hand and tried to make it make sense. It was bought last night, but now it was empty and thrown away here, in David's office, while everyone else was outside. Why?

You didn't know what any of it meant on its own. You only knew it was wrong, and you knew you weren't supposed to be the one finding it.

You put it back exactly where it had been and wiped your hands on your pants even though there was nothing on them.]

(live: 14s)[(stop:)When you came back outside the air still had that wrong cold to it and nothing had changed.

[[You rejoined the others->Morning-Bottleneck]]]


:: Morning {"position":"400,500","size":"100,100"}
From the moment you stepped out of your car, the air felt wrong, a cold that didn't belong to the forecast, sitting on your skin and refusing to lift. Across the parking lot, in the open bay of David's garage, Samael stood beside the car. Not moving. Just standing there.

(live: 4s)[(stop:)When you finally reached him, you understood why he wasn't moving. David sat slumped in the driver's seat, head tipped back, eyes closed. For a confused half second you thought he was asleep. Then the rest of it registered: the closed garage, the key still in the ignition, the stale chemical weight of the air. The realization arrived slowly and then all at once, and the chill on your skin became something else entirely.]

(live: 8s)[(stop:)You must have stepped back from the car. You don't remember it. Somewhere behind you a voice was saying your name, and another voice was saying nothing at all. The parking lot was filling up the way it always did on a Wednesday, except nothing about this was Wednesday anymore.]

(live: 11s)[(stop:)David had the ticket. You all agreed on it last night, half joking and half not. He'd hold it until the claim office opened Wednesday morning, because David was the only one of you nobody would suspect of running off with it. It was probably in his wallet, three feet from where you were standing. Nobody had mentioned it yet. Somebody would.]

(live: 15s)[(stop:)The morning refuses to hold still in your head. You try to walk it back and it comes apart in your hands, four pieces that will not line up. Who had arrived just as you had? Who was already there?

Where do your thoughts land first?

* [[Samael, alone by the car when you first pulled in->M-B-0]]
* [[A quiet minute in David's office, while no one was watching->M-D-0]]
* [[Arriving alongside Abby->M-A-0]]
* [[Cassandra, already talking, impossible to interrupt->M-C-0]]]


:: Morning-Bottleneck {"position":"1100,500","size":"100,100"}
The morning won't stay as one thing.

You can hold onto pieces of it. Moments that felt clear while they were happening.

They don't fit together the way they should.
{
(if: $viewed's length is 1)[There’s still something you haven’t seen from the inside. You could go back, stand somewhere else in it, listen to someone else.<br>]

(if: $viewed's length is 2)[You’ve already been through it twice. There’s one piece left you haven’t stood inside. You could reach for it, or leave it where it is.<br>]

(if: $viewed's length is 3)[You’ve seen enough of it to know it won’t become one version. Not cleanly.<br>]

(if: $viewed's length < 3)[What do you reach for?<br>]

(if: not ($viewed contains "MA") and $viewed's length < 3)[[[Arriving alongside Abby->M-A-0]]<br>]

(if: not ($viewed contains "MB") and $viewed's length < 3)[[[Samael, alone by the car->M-B-0]]<br>]

(if: not ($viewed contains "MC") and $viewed's length < 3)[[[Cassandra on the curb->M-C-0]]<br>]

(if: not ($viewed contains "MD") and $viewed's length < 3)[[[A quiet minute in David's office->M-D-0]]<br>]
}
[[Let the day keep going->Evening]]


:: Review {"position":"2100,500","size":"100,100"}
You try to hold it in place.

Not all of it. Just enough that it stays for more than a second at a time.

Pieces come back wrong.

Things people said that didn't line up, not at first. They sounded fine when you heard them. They only start to shift when you set them next to each other.

(if: $saw_pills and $heard_abby_errand and $saw_abby_rewrite)[
The pills.

Bought last night. Gone this morning. Left in David's office like they didn't belong to anyone.

Abby leaving right after the numbers came up. Before she talked to anyone.

And tonight, Samael saying he asked her to go.

It doesn't sit.

(set: $clues_found to it + 1)
]

(if: $saw_A_influence_B)[
That sentence.

You heard it twice.

Once from Cassandra, like something she remembered in passing. And once from Samael, like it was something he already knew how to say.

The same words. The same shape.

It pulls the same way, both times.
]

You can keep turning it over.

Or you can leave it there.

[[You continue with your day->Aftermath]]


